                            <comment id="15693478" author="nsyca" created="Thu, 24 Nov 2016 14:57:21 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Note that correlated predicates in the right operand of the FOJ is not a problem because it is protected in the block of code below in &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;private&lt;/span&gt; def pullOutCorrelatedPredicates( ... )
...
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;case&lt;/span&gt; j @ Join(_, right, jt, _) &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; !jt.isInstanceOf[InnerLike] =&amp;gt;
          failOnOuterReference(j)
          failOnOuterReferenceInSubTree(right, &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&quot;a LEFT (OUTER) JOIN&quot;&lt;/span&gt;)
          j
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, the error message is misleading as it reports an error on a LEFT JOIN.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;Accessing &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;outer&lt;/span&gt; query column is not allowed in a LEFT (OUTER) JOIN: 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I propose to block the incorrect result case in the FOJ at this moment and change the misleading error message case.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
